I teach them not to limit themselves on what they could do with a plain pencil. All of our teachers here at Cercicon in Luanda can teach but very few of them understand the importance of entering competitions, so what I have done is to encourage them to apply for these competitions and I even go as far as guiding them through the process – nothing in life is easy to attain but if you want it, you have to be prepared to work for it.”

"I am going to approach other academic institutions and offer to teach my course, which no other college or university does. I want to see it work and succeed in other countries such as Tanzania, Kenya and Nigeria - and maybe, when I’m old the student have come full circle and take up the course themselves.”

Traditional African culinary courses are a delight to be part of, so if you’re in Luanda…
